Have you double checked your cable? We had similar problems with corrupt firmware’s caused by a bad image due to a bad cable (especially since the error message says corrupt firmware cannot run). We were able to use an ethernet cable to image our RoboRIO 1 by setting its IP to 172.22.11.2.

If you want to try this, open up windows run (windows + r), and enter ncpa.cpl.

On the network adapters, disable ALL other network adapters (wifi, bluetooth), but just ethernet. Right click on the only ethernet adapter still available, and hit properties.
.

Click on the Internet Protocol Version 4, and hit properties.

Set it to the following settings:

This will make the ethernet cable use the same IP as connecting over USB.

At this point, you should use the UPDATE FIRMWARE option on the imaging tool to reinstall the firmware onto the RoboRIO. If this succeeds, then use the format target option to install the FRC OS. Hopefully this should fix your issue.

REMINDER: Remember to set the IP for the adapter back to obtaining an IP address automatically after you do these steps!!

Oh, and if these steps work, then get a new tether (its a USB-A to USB-B cable, also commonly called a printer cable)
